<subSubSection id="5CAC2C791A0FC5472E980C03D923F9B5" pageId="1" pageNumber="22" type="comments">
<paragraph id="E38058B9CC84C69D4A8DF88448A6ED5C" pageId="1" pageNumber="22">Comments</paragraph>
<paragraph id="BAE934CC2F4A181DBB3F4E5756645061" pageId="1" pageNumber="22">
Spach had to chose a new name for this Linnaean species because 
<taxonomicName id="7909C81CAA18DDFBF853AEA49489FE11" authority="staphisagria" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ranunculaceae" genus="Staphisagria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Ranunculales" pageId="1" pageNumber="22" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="staphisagria">
<emphasis id="0BA1FEF9C5FDA409CA0C1C6DF22457DD" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="22">Staphisagria staphisagria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
would be an exact tautonym (not permitted in botanical nomenclature), and since his misspelling of 
<normalizedToken id="3505A21E17A64BCBE544A4BD9B318B67" originalValue="Hill’s">Hill's</normalizedToken>
genus (as 
<taxonomicName id="354BD4055AD321FD594291477ABB6C6F" authorityName="Spach" authorityYear="1839" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ranunculaceae" genus="Staphysagria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Ranunculales" pageId="1" pageNumber="22" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="0D0386FA405EDDB679E02F3DBC33DE04" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="22">Staphysagria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) is a correctable error (variant spelling), 
<normalizedToken id="32E7A28FE6CF85F6E72E412CA37D54E5" originalValue="Spach’s">Spach's</normalizedToken>
name 
<taxonomicName id="A189F24DB1540FCD22E7C59619BCEBE5" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ranunculaceae" genus="Staphisagria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Ranunculales" pageId="1" pageNumber="22" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="macrosperma">
<emphasis id="9708F9666861555963B8226480A96B78" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="22">Staphisagria macrosperma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is legitimate. Among the three species of the genus 
<taxonomicName id="694718ECB4FA26E538FF1397A7F8E81F" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ranunculaceae" genus="Staphisagria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Ranunculales" pageId="1" pageNumber="22" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="35618BD0863D19EE1A93A3F895340BD3" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="22">Staphisagria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="FAC28AB9414CFFA57AE7E1ABE87F7798" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ranunculaceae" genus="Staphisagria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Ranunculales" pageId="1" pageNumber="22" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="macrospermahas">
<emphasis id="7282126A8DDE5440E8B88FC670BBE302" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="22">Staphisagria macrospermahas</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the largest distribution. Because of its ancient use in medicine (
<bibRefCitation id="B99994F96435ABCAB17602D6B4274F45" author="Cristofolini, G" journalOrPublisher="Taxon" pageId="1" pageNumber="22" pagination="305 - 319" publicationUrl="doi: 10.2307/1223760" refId="B5" refString="Cristofolini, G, Mossetti, U, 1998. Interpretation of plant names in a late medieval medical treatise. Taxon 47: 305 - 319, doi: 10.2307/1223760" title="Interpretation of plant names in a late medieval medical treatise." url="doi: 10.2307/1223760" volume="47" year="1998">Cristofolini and Mossetti 1998</bibRefCitation>
), it is found all around the Mediterranean basin (
<bibRefCitation id="FC0F9DD8F845BF3C089CD7297DDE3342" author="Greuter, W" journalOrPublisher="Collectanea Botanica (Barcelona)" pageId="1" pageNumber="22" refId="B9" refString="Greuter, W, Burdet, H, Long, G, 1989. Med-Checklist, vol. 4 (Lauraceae-Rhamnaceae). Editions des Conservatoire et Jardin Botaniques de Geneve, Geneva. ." title="Med-Checklist, vol. 4 (Lauraceae-Rhamnaceae). Editions des Conservatoire et Jardin Botaniques de Geneve, Geneva." year="1989">Greuter et al. 1989</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="E1013BF26ABEE0E7FFA6965F3794C1BC" author="Orellana, M" journalOrPublisher="Genetica" pageId="1" pageNumber="22" pagination="221 - 232" publicationUrl="doi: 10.1007/s10709–008–9271–9" refId="B16" refString="Orellana, M, Lopez-Pujol, J, Blanche, C, Rovira, A, Bosch, M, 2009a. Genetic diversity in Delphinium staphisagria (Ranunculaceae), a rare Mediterranean dysploid larkspur with medicinal uses. Genetica 135: 221 - 232, doi: 10.1007/s10709-008-9271-9" title="Genetic diversity in Delphinium staphisagria (Ranunculaceae), a rare Mediterranean dysploid larkspur with medicinal uses." url="doi: 10.1007/s10709–008–9271–9" volume="135" year="2009 a">Orellana et al. 2009a</bibRefCitation>
). It grows in rocky areas, and is adapted to nitrophilous and disturbed habitats (
<bibRefCitation id="75312CD39B4397600903A0F0E9DE8343" author="Orellana, M" journalOrPublisher="Genetica" pageId="1" pageNumber="22" pagination="221 - 232" publicationUrl="doi: 10.1007/s10709–008–9271–9" refId="B16" refString="Orellana, M, Lopez-Pujol, J, Blanche, C, Rovira, A, Bosch, M, 2009a. Genetic diversity in Delphinium staphisagria (Ranunculaceae), a rare Mediterranean dysploid larkspur with medicinal uses. Genetica 135: 221 - 232, doi: 10.1007/s10709-008-9271-9" title="Genetic diversity in Delphinium staphisagria (Ranunculaceae), a rare Mediterranean dysploid larkspur with medicinal uses." url="doi: 10.1007/s10709–008–9271–9" volume="135" year="2009 a">Orellana et al. 2009a</bibRefCitation>
). Figure 2 shows key morphological characteristics of 
<taxonomicName id="F839C76DBB94EEE4CA6B3CEE3B29CDBB" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ranunculaceae" genus="Staphisagria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Ranunculales" pageId="1" pageNumber="22" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="macrosperma">
<emphasis id="86480AD52217995BF9F48735FCE01A8D" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="22">Staphisagria macrosperma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
